OL,3,CScottish Conservative peer defects to
OL,4,CReform UK
OL,6,FDiscussing his experiences with the
OL,7,FScottish Tories, the former minister
OL,8,Fsaid: "What I found, quite candidly,
OL,9,Fis a party which is regional not
OL,10,Fnational, parochial not political,
OL,11,Ftimid not ambitious; a party without a
OL,12,Fvision of how to govern Scotland with
OL,13,Fa right-of-centre agenda."
OL,15,FHe previously stood for Holyrood in
OL,16,F2021 in the Lothian region but
OL,17,Ffinished fifth.
